Following lengthy investigations, the Hawks&rsquo; Commercial Wing arrested a 42 year old Tax practitioner for fraud.It is alleged that between 2009 and 2012 the suspect would approach unsuspecting SARS clients, undertake to assist them in submitting their returns and then submitted fictitious business financial statements as well as false business expenses/losses as supporting documents. Upon the refund materialising he would then allegedly pocket large sums.He is expected to appear at the Bellville Commercial Crimes Court.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.